{{Infobox baseball biography |image=Ed Porray.jpg |name=Ed Porray |position=[[Pitcher]] |bats=Right |throws=Right |birth_date={{Birth date|1888|12|5}} |birth_place=A ship on the [[Atlantic Ocean]] |death_date={{death date and age|1954|7|13|1888|12|5}} |death_place=[[Lackawaxen, Pennsylvania]] |debutleague = MLB |debutdate=April 17 |debutyear=1914 |debutteam=[[Buffalo Buffeds/Blues|Buffalo Buffeds]] |finalleague = MLB |finaldate=May 1 |finalyear=1914 |finalteam=[[Buffalo Buffeds/Blues|Buffalo Buffeds]] |statleague = MLB |stat1label=[[Win–loss record (pitching)|Win–loss record]] |stat1value=0-1 |stat2label=[[Earned run average]] |stat2value=4.35 |stat3label=[[Strikeout]]s |stat3value=0 |teams= *[[Buffalo Buffeds/Blues|Buffalo Buffeds]] ({{By|1914}}) }} '''Edmund Joseph Porray''' (December 5, 1888 – July 13, 1954) was a [[Major League Baseball|major league]] [[pitcher]]. A right-handed pitcher who had a brief Major League career in which he pitched in 3 games for the {{By|1914}} [[Buffalo Buffeds/Blues|Buffalo Buffeds]] of the [[Federal League]], compiling a 0–1 record with a 4.35 [[earned run average]] in 10{{fraction|1|3}} innings pitched.<ref name=retrosheet>{{cite web|title= Ed Porray's Stats|work = retrosheet.org | url=http://www.retrosheet.org/boxesetc/P/Pporre101.htm | accessdate =2008-03-21}}</ref>
Today, Porray is best remembered for his unusual birthplace, as he is the only Major League Baseball player to have been [[List of people born at sea|born at sea]]. His birth certificate lists "At sea, on the [[Atlantic Ocean]]" as his birthplace.<ref name="atsea">{{cite web| title = Famous First Foreign Born Baseball Players | work = baseball-almanac.com | url=http://www.baseball-almanac.com/firsts/first13.shtml | accessdate = 2008-03-21 }}</ref>
Porray died at the age of 65 in [[Lackawaxen, Pennsylvania]], and is interred at the [[Odd Fellows]] Cemetery in that town.<ref name=retrosheet/>
