The '''murder of Bobby Äikiä''' (12 March 1995 – 14 January 2006) occurred in [[Sweden]], when Äikiä, a 10-year-old [[Swedes|Swedish]] boy, was [[Murder|murdered]] by his mother and stepfather. He suffered from [[Fragile X syndrome]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.svd.se/dynamiskt/inrikes/did_12604441.asp |title=Flytt raserade tryggheten |work=[[Svenska Dagbladet]] |language=Swedish |accessdate=12 December 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009180637/http://www.svd.se/dynamiskt/inrikes/did_12604441.asp |archivedate=October 9, 2007 }}</ref> Äikiä was left to freeze after being tied to a chair and thrown out of his house by his stepfather Eddy Larsson. He was reported missing by his mother Niina Äikiä, who claimed he had disappeared after a visit to the Bäckebol shopping centre near [[Gothenburg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.svd.se/dynamiskt/inrikes/did_11689671.asp |title=Pojke försvunnen i Göteborg |work=[[Svenska Dagbladet]] |language=Swedish |accessdate=12 December 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929131435/http://www.svd.se/dynamiskt/inrikes/did_11689671.asp |archivedate=September 29, 2007 }}</ref> Soldiers from the [[Swedish Armed Forces]] searched for Äikiä, but when a body could not be found, suspicion turned towards his mother. Äikiä's body was found under the ice of a nearby lake following his mother's confession. Both parents were sentenced to ten years' [[imprisonment]] in June 2006 for involuntary [[manslaughter]] and mistreating a child.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/vss/nyheter/story/0,2789,872352,00.html|title=Gråter öppet i rätten|work=[[Aftonbladet]]|language=Swedish|accessdate=12 December 2010}}{{dead link|date=February 2017}}</ref> The murder and the following debate led to ''Lex Bobby'', a law that requires a child protection investigation when a child has died as a result of violence.<ref>[https://sverigesradio.se/sida/avsnitt/797023?programid=1316 Lex Bobby - det skulle inte få hända igen]</ref>
In February 2008, Niina Äikiä received 54,000 [[Swedish krona|kronor]] in compensation after being attacked and cut in the face inside the prison.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.aftonbladet.se/nyheter/article11355561.ab|title=Bobbys mamma får 54 000 i skadestånd|website=[[Aftonbladet]]|language=Swedish|access-date=9 November 2015}}</ref>
