'''Ruslan Adilkhanovich Dibirghadzhiyev''' ({{lang-az|Ruslan Dibirhacıyev}}, {{lang-ru|Руслан Адилханович Дибиргаджиев}}; born 20 July 1988, [[Dagestan]]) is a [[Avars (Caucasus)|Avar]] [[Russia]]n [[naturalized]] [[Azerbaijani people|Azerbaijani]] [[freestyle wrestler]]. He competed at the 70&nbsp;kg division in the [[2014 European Wrestling Championships]] and won the gold medal<ref>[http://awf-az.org/en/x-b-rl-r/avropa-empionati/item/2879-saerbaest-zhulaesh-y-ghmam-z-avropa-ikindzisi-oldu-foto-video Sərbəst güləş yığmamız Avropa ikincisi oldu / FOTO-VİDEO] {{ref-az}}</ref> after beating [[Grigor Grigoryan]] of [[Armenia]].

