'''Yang Jingren''' ({{zh|楊靜仁}}, [[Xiao'erjing]]: {{lang|zh-Arab|ﻳْﺎ  دٍ ژٌ}}) (1918 – October 19, 2001) was a [[People's Republic of China]] politician. A member of the [[Hui people]] ethnic group, he was born in [[Lanzhou]], [[Gansu]] Province. He was the head of the [[United Front Work Department]] from 1982 to 1985.

